"BRIK" - BRICS Currency Could Shake Dollar Dominance and Weaken It

"Most likely, it will be done," said Deputy Chairman of the State Duma Alexander Babakov, responding to a question about whether BRICS countries can start printing a single currency.

The introduction of a new currency can smooth out exchange rate volatility, minimize the impact of monetary policy actions by major central banks (such as the US Federal Reserve and the European Central Bank) on export-import flows within BRICS.

The creation of a new currency is expected on August 22 in Johannesburg. In addition, a decision is expected to be made on the admission of a large number of new countries to BRICS (more than 30 applications).
